An Internet-ID Code is a 12-digit number assigned to a remote Host. When using an
Internet-ID connection
, this code serves as the address of the remote computer.
Related links:
Getting Started
The
MSI Configurator
is an integrated tool designed to assist you in generating a custom Host or Agent installer for deploying across your remote computers. With the MSI Configurator, you can tailor the installer to meet your specific requirements.
Related links:
